Pour milk into large bowl. Add pudding mixes. Beat with wire whisk 2 minutes or until well blended. Let stand 3 minutes. Gently stir in 1-1/2 cups of the whipped topping. Place 15 of the wafers on bottom of 2-quart serving bowl. Top with half each of the bananas and pudding mixture. Repeat layers ending with pudding mixture. Cover with remaining whipped topping. Refrigerate at least 1 hour or until ready to serve.